{"id":12098,"name":"Final Blow","slug":"final-blow","url":"https:\/\/www.igdb.com\/games\/final-blow","created_at":1441184771258,"updated_at":1517270919841,"summary":"Final Blow is a boxing arcade game created in 1988 by Taito. The name would remain the same for all ported platforms, except for the Sega Mega Drive\/Genesis versions, which Sega released outside Japan as James 'Buster' Douglas Knockout Boxing featuring Buster Douglas himself in 1990 immediately after his victory over Mike Tyson. \n \nThe game is essentially a side scrolling boxing game where the player moves left and right to control a screen sized boxer. When the timing is right, the player can unleash a final blow punch which can sometimes KO the opponent in a single strike. The home versions contained a spectator mode where the player can watch their favorite boxers compete.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[22690,26772,11253,8674,40885,15851,34919,55715,37175,18417],"tags":[1,32,268435470,536871544,536872078,536875054,536875138,536875359,536875360,536876210,1073741828],"developers":[1440],"publishers":[13104,7175,1440],"category":0,"player_perspectives":[4],"game_modes":[1,2],"keywords":[632,1166,4142,4226,4447,4448,5298],"themes":[1,32],"genres":[14],"first_release_date":631065600000,"platforms":[29,52,63,118,16,15],"release_dates":[{"category":2,"platform":118,"date":662601600000,"region":5,"human":"1990","y":1990,"m":12},{"category":2,"platform":15,"date":694137600000,"region":1,"human":"1991","y":1991,"m":12},{"category":2,"platform":63,"date":694137600000,"region":1,"human":"1991","y":1991,"m":12},{"category":2,"platform":16,"date":694137600000,"region":1,"human":"1991","y":1991,"m":12},{"category":2,"platform":52,"date":631065600000,"region":5,"human":"1989","y":1989,"m":12},{"category":0,"platform":29,"date":638150400000,"region":5,"human":"1990-Mar-23","y":1990,"m":3}],"alternative_names":[{"name":"James 'Buster' Douglas Knockout Boxing","comment":"Sega Genesis Title"}],"screenshots